history.content: You'll need permission to enrol in the grad version of the class, which generally isn't possible if there's an undergrad version of the class. The differences between the undergrad and grad version are variable, but they tend to differ by at least a final project in my experience.

I'm currently a senior entering my last semester at UC Berkeley. I noticed that some classes that have both undergrad and grad options (100 level classes and 200 level classes) have no undergrad seats open, but still have some space in the grad version. Can I take the grad version of this class or do I have to wait for space to potentially open up in the undergrad version? Is there generally some meaningful difference between being enrolled in the grad version versus the undergrad version?
history.subject: Grad version of classes?
